                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="avery_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1918-80) a US <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/cartoonist#cartoonist_topg_1" title="cartoonist definition"><span class="ndv">cartoonist</span></a>. He created the characters of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/daffy-ducktm#daffy_duck_topg_1" title="Daffy Duck definition"><span class="ndv">Daffy Duck</span></a> (1937), <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bugs-bunnytm#bugs_bunny_topg_1" title="Bugs Bunny definition"><span class="ndv">Bugs Bunny</span></a> (1940) and Droopy (1943). He later joined <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hanna-and-barbera" title="Hanna and Barbera definition"><span class="ndv">Hanna and Barbera</span></a> for the television series <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-flintstones" title="The Flintstones definition"><span class="ndv">The Flintstones</span></a>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
